-- Ghana 91-day bill yield rises to 24.0822 percent
-- By Kwasi Kpodo
-- Fri Jun 20, 2014 01:35PM EDT
-- None



ACCRA, June 20 (Reuters) - The Bank of Ghana said the yield on its 91-day bill rose to a fresh three-year high of 24.0822 percent at Friday's auction, from 24.0552 percent at the last sale.

The Bank said it accepted 589.72 million cedis ($185.73 million) worth of bids out of the 589.74 million worth of bids tendered for the 91-day paper. For full details please click here:   http://www.bog.gov.gh/privatecontent/Treasury/Auctresults%201386.pdf